---
title: Pad’s Thai with Tamarind and Roasted Peanuts
description: It took our chef Patrick awhile to get around to this little classic because we wanted to get it just right. Our version of the famous Pad Thai uses egg noodles (for ease of cooking) and one of the key flavours - tamarind. Originally from Africa, tamarind has that sweet and sour flavour we most commonly associate with this dish. Sprinkle on some crushed, dry roasted peanuts for added texture and you may as well be strolling through the street markets on the Khao San Road. If you like it hot then add the whole chilli, otherwise just add as much as you dare!
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/55d3577ff8b25ea41e8b4567.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.co.uk/recipecards/card/55d3577ff8b25ea41e8b4567.pdf
